In a Dockerfile, both ADD and COPY are used to copy files and directories into a Docker image â€” but they differ in functionality and use cases.

1. COPY
Purpose: Simple, transparent file copying.
Feature	Description -- Copies	Files/directories from source to image
Source	Must be local
No Extras	Does not extract archives or fetch URLs

Example:
COPY ./app /usr/src/app
ğŸ“Œ Use when you just want to copy files or directories from your build context to the image.
